    dc:creator "Baldwin, Carole C.", "Bertoncini, Athila", "Carvalho-Filho, Alfredo", "Fischer, Luciano G.", "Garcia, Lucas Canes", "Robertson, D. Ross", "Sampaio, Claudio L. S.", "Silva, Jodir Pereira Da" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Generic reassignment of Centropristis fuscula Poey, 1861 (Teleostei: Serranidae), with re-description of the species and comments on its geographical range and sexual system" ;
    bibo:endPage "73" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-09-15" ;
    bibo:startPage "51" ;
    bibo:volume "5346" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353037>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353043>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353045>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353049> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353037>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Linear correlation between depth of collection and size of Serranus fusculus. Gray dots denote specimens identified as post-larvae or juveniles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8353037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Serranus fusculus. A) AZUSC 5962, 159 mm SL, female, Bahia, Brazil, 2008; B) fresh specimen, off Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, pictured in Bernardes et al., 2005; C) fresh specimen, off Natal, Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil, stationARMT53B, pictured in Lins Oliveira et al., 2015; D) Holotype, MCZ 10015, male, 141 mm SL, Havana, Cuba,1864. E) Radiograph, NPM 2458, 125 mm SL, off Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, depth 186 m. Images by Sampaio, C.L.S. (A); Fischer, L.G. (B, C, E); Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University © President and Fellows of Harvard College (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8353043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353045>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Otoliths from right side of Serranus fusculus with 200 mm TL, 188 mm FL, and 105 g TW in superior (A), inner (B), and outer view (C). TW=total weight, TL=total length, FL=fork length." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8353045/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8353049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Histological section of specimen MZUSP 71061, in which the synchronous development of testicular (1) portions, containing spermatozoa in the spermatic duct, and ovarian (2) portions, containing oocytes at an advanced stage of development, can be observed. Staining: HE. Scale bar=150 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8353049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

